{"lemma":"مِحْجَنَيْ","slug":"مِحْجَنَيْ","root":"ح.ج.ن","root_slug":"ح-ج-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ج-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7245"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7245","headword_ar":"مِحْجَنٌ","root":"Hjn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved, staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHojanapN","text_ar":"مِحْجَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh, Ham p. 403,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Ham,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hooked, head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked at the end,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawolajaAn","text_ar":"صَوْلَجَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, Msb, Ham:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one draws towards him with it the extremities"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the branches"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of trees, and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ubi suprà:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a stick with a crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved, end, being naturally so on the tree on which it has grown;"},{"kind":"text","text":"distinguished from a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SwljAn","text_ar":"صولجان"},{"kind":"text","text":", the end of which is crooked, or curved, artificially: (T:) or, accord. to AZ,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any stick with a curved head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAjinu","text_ar":"مَحَاجِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) The appellation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibu","text_ar":"صَاحِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmiHojani","text_ar":"المِحْجَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The owner of the crooked stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"] was given to a certain man who, in the Time of Ignorance, used to sit in the highway, and take with his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHjn","text_ar":"محجن"},{"kind":"text","text":"one thing after another, of the goods of the passers-by; and if any one were cognizant of his doing, he excused himself, saying that the thing had caught to his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHjn","text_ar":"محجن"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":523},{"kind":"text","text":"You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yarokuDu AlmiHojana","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يَرْكُضُ المِحْجَنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one will not kick the crooked stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is of no use,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stands one in no stead:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the saying originating from the fact that a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHjn","text_ar":"محجن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put between the hind legs of the camel, and if he be inert, or wanting in vigour, he will not kick it; but if he be sharp in spirit, he will kick it and go on. (TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lamiHojanu maAlK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَمِحْجَنُ مَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who puts the cattle into a good state, and pastures and manages them well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A brand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mark made with a hot iron, upon a camel, in the form of a line with a crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hooked, end, like the stick so called."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHojiynN","text_ar":"تَحْجِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  And The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hooked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bill"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bird; because of its crookedness. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","IAth","Ham","Msb","Mgh","S","T"]}]}}